article.description: — Anderson Mirambeaux scored 24 points as Miami (OH) beat Bowling Green 74-65 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Miami (OH) wins 74-65 against Bowling Green
article.story:
OXFORD, Ohio -- — Anderson Mirambeaux scored 24 points as Miami (OH) beat Bowling Green 74-65 on Tuesday night.

Mirambeaux had eight rebounds for the RedHawks (10-18, 4-11 Mid-American Conference). Mekhi Lairy scored 13 points while going 4 of 10 from the floor, including 1 for 5 from distance, and 4 for 4 from the line, and added seven assists. Kamari Williams recorded nine points and finished 3 of 6 from 3-point range.

The Falcons (10-18, 4-11) were led by Samari Curtis, who recorded 17 points and three steals. Chandler Turner added 10 points and two steals for Bowling Green. Leon Ayers III also had nine points, nine rebounds and six assists. The Falcons prolonged their losing streak to eight in a row.

NEXT UP

Both teams play on Saturday. Miami (OH) hosts Ohio while Bowling Green hosts Kent State.

------
